>>>>>>>>>>>>>> otherwise wouldn't
>>>>>>>>>>>>>> be allowed to already hold the dma-resv lock. That's the 
>>>>>>>>>>>>>> fix I
>>>>>>>>>>>>>> was referring to
>>>>>>>>>>>>>> earlier.
>>>>>>>>>>>>> Yeah, I can see the need for a dedicated lock for the 
>>>>>>>>>>>>> GEM's gpuva
>>>>>>>>>>>>> list, but
>>>>>>>>>>>>> holding the vm's dma-resv lock across the unlink shouldn't 
